public class PrimitiveArrayPointer extends Memory

A pointer to a memory block containing one or more values of a primitive type.

  • Method Details

    • ints

      public static PrimitiveArrayPointer ints(int arraySize)

      Creates an empty PrimitiveArrayPointer containing primitive int values.

      Use toIntArray(int[]) or getIntAt(int) to access the array data.

      Parameters:
      arraySize - The number of elements to allocate space for.
      Returns:
      A PrimitiveArrayPointer of the specified size pointing to an "empty" memory block.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - If the specified type has no public no-arg constructor, if its size is zero, or if its size cannot be determined.

    • floats
